node.title: Four arrested after protesters allegedly try to enter Parliament House in Canberra
node.description: Four people are arrested and police use capsicum spray to disperse protesters after a group of them allegedly tried to enter Parliament House in Canberra.
node.content: ["Four people have been arrested and police have used capsicum spray to disperse\u00a0protesters\u00a0after a group of them allegedly tried to enter Parliament House in Canberra this morning.", "ACT Policing said three men and a woman were taken to the ACT\u00a0Watch House when a small group of demonstrators approached the building.", "Police allege they were trying to enter the building to protest unlawfully.", "The group of about 30 to 40 people\u00a0appeared to be protesting about Indigenous sovereignty and Australia's COVID-19 vaccination policy.", "OC spray, also known as capsicum spray, was used by ACT Policing and Australian Federal Police protective service officers in an attempt to disperse the crowd.", "No charges have yet been laid.", "The arrests follow\u00a0a number of other protests that have been taking place\u00a0at Old Parliament House in recent weeks, including two instances where the building was set alight.", "The actions of the\u00a0protesters\u00a0have been denounced by the nearby Aboriginal tent embassy and local Aboriginal elders\u00a0as they prepare to mark the 50th anniversary of the\u00a0tent embassy, which was established on Australia Day in 1972.", "A 30-year-old Victorian man has been charged with arson and damaging Commonwealth property over the second fire at Old Parliament House\u00a0on December\u00a030.", "The fire\u00a0badly damaged the doors and charred the outdoor portico beyond repair."]
